      <section class="grid_outer chapter">
  <h1 class="chapter-title">Delightful details
      </h1>

  <div class="chapter-content">
        
        <div class="chapter-intro">
      <section class="moduleD1">
    <div class="module-body">
    <p>Animation can exist within all components of an app and at all scales, from finely detailed icons to key transitions and actions. All elements work together to construct a seamless experience and a beautiful, functional app.</p><p>The most basic use of animation is in transitions, but an app can truly delight a user when animation is used in ways beyond the obvious. A menu icon that becomes an arrow or playback controls that smoothly change from one to the other serve dual functions: to inform the user and to imbue your app with a moment of wonder and a sense of superb craftsmanship. Users do notice such small details.</p>
  </div>
